Bolaji Ogundele, Abuja  President Muhammadu Buhari would be addressing the country at 7:00pm on Monday. A statement from the State House, signed by Special Adviser to the President, Mr Femi Adesina, said the nationwide broadcast would be aired by the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) and the Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN). “President Muhammadu Buhari will broadcast to the nation Monday, April 13, 2020 at 7pm. “Television, radio and other electronic media outlets are enjoined to hook up to the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) and Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN) respectively for the broadcast,” the statement said.